channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: What’s Stopping a Deal in Gaza?
item.description: Washington now sees Benjamin Netanyahu as the chief obstacle.

item.title: Paetongtarn Shinawatra Is Chosen as Thailand’s New Prime Minister
item.description: The abrupt rise of the scion of a powerful and polarizing political family is widely seen as a continuation of the meddling that has undermined Thai democracy.

item.title: People are getting rich in Dubai despite Middle East conflict
item.description: Dubai's economy is buzzing with tourism and construction as it positions itself as a safe haven in a region that's resting on a knife’s edge.

item.title: Cease-Fire Talks Enter 2nd Day With Wide Gaps Between Israel and Hamas
item.description: Hamas officials are not participating directly in the talks but have signaled a willingness to consider new proposals from Israel.

item.title: Investors, entrepreneurs, and good ideas are becoming collateral damage as the U.S. and China battle over dual-use tech
item.description: Nearly every civilian technology could be adapted to have military applications, which makes innovation increasingly complex and contentious.

item.title: Ukraine’s Push Into Russia Met Early Success. Where Does It Go From Here?
item.description: Ukraine’s forces could try advancing farther on Russian soil, or return to the front line, where Moscow is making gains. There are arguments for various options.

item.description: The World Health Organization warned the virus might ultimately spill across international borders.

item.description: Plus, charges in Matthew Perry’s death.

item.title: Who Is Paetongtarn Shinawatra, Thailand’s New Prime Minister?
item.description: The political heir to an influential family is now leading Thailand with no governing experience in a tumultuous time.

item.title: Ed Sheeran bought a 1.4% stake in his boyhood Premier League club Ipswich Town, bagging him executive suite access
item.description: The minority 1.4% stake won't see Sheeran join the board, but will secure him access to an executive box.

item.title: Russia Closes In on Key Eastern Ukrainian City Despite Kursk Incursion
item.description: A Russian advance toward Pokrovsk casts doubts on Ukraine’s hopes that its offensive in western Russia will prompt Moscow to scale back attacks elsewhere.

item.title: Bavarian Nordic gearing up to produce 10 million doses of mpox vaccine as ‘further imported cases’ in Europe are coming, WHO warns
item.description: Sweden announced the first mpox case outside Africa, the day after the WHO declared a global health emergency.
